<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06301042 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06301042 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: (Corey Emery)  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  BERKELEY; OAKLAND; EAST-BAY; FIRE; DISASTER; VICTIM; PROFILE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  'WHEN the black smoke started coming up and the explosions started, we ran. .. . We abandoned one car and got into the other one. I knew some back roads. .. . It was difficult getting out. There were traffic jams. It must have takena half hour. If there had been flames here, people would have died by thescore. . . . I watched as the fire started creeping in around. And then atabout 4 in the morning, I came back, . . . and it was a smoldering red ruin.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Perspective  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  'IT WAS A . . . RUIN'  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  A Perspective Special Section; See related stories pages 1D and 4-7D,Editorial page 8D, and Commentaries page 9D.; Corey Emery, Physician's Asst.;Corey Emery moved into his Broadway Terrace house three weeks ago and hadn'tmade his first mortgage payment. He had saved 20 years to buy it.  </MEMO><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911027  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  7D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  149  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday, October 27, 199100301042,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>